This is another idea. How about an application that takes a clumsy decimal representation of an irrational number, ie 1.41421356237
and cycles through powers to find the irrational number that it's likely to represent.

This would only be useful for college students who want to cheat at trigonometry. But it's an application we could create and put up online.

Let's start running my raspberry pi as a server, so we can start hosting content this spring break. 
